2026-04-21 01:37:19 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) 3 (n end connection to switch of Control Module 3)'] hypothesis_explanation='Diagnostics localized the remaining fault to Control Module 3. With a good 12 V battery, 12 V is present up to the input of CM3, but drops to ~0 V at CM3’s output and throughout the rest of the chain. Internal probing of CM3 shows 12 V at the connected end of Control Input Cable (+) 3, but essentially 0 V at the switch node and output despite the switch itself having normal continuity (~0.01 Ω). The test further notes that the ‘n’ end of Control Input Cable (+) 3 is floating and no longer connected to the switch, meaning the series 12 V path is open at this point. Therefore the root cause is an open / disconnected joint of Control Input Cable (+) 3 at its connection to the switch inside Control Module 3. Restoring/repairing this connection should re-establish 12 V through the rest of the modules and allow the lamp and indicators to operate normally.'
