description: With the new, known-good battery installed and the PSU LED still off, use a multimeter to measure DC voltage between the two outgoing PSU terminals (the two cables that feed the rest of the chain). If 12 V is present there, move sequentially along the series chain: disconnect at the input of control module 1 and measure across its incoming pair, then across its outgoing pair toward module 2, and so on, until the load module input. Note at which point (between which two modules) the 12 V disappears. This will localize an open circuit, misconnection, or polarity swap between modules., outcome='12 V is present at the PSU output and remains present through Control Module 2’s output, and at the positive input of Control Module 3. The voltage has dropped to near 0 V by Control Module 3’s output and remains near 0 V through the rest of the chain to the load. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED in the measured cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=720.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 3 (internal circuit and switch path),
description: Open the inspection panel of Control Module 3. With all modules still wired as before and the good battery installed, place the multimeter negative probe on the module’s 0 V line and the positive probe on (a) the incoming 12 V terminal, (b) the switch input node, (c) the switch output node, and (d) the outgoing 12 V terminal. With the switch in ON and then OFF positions, record the voltages and check for continuity across the switch and any obvious damage or loose connections in the series path., outcome="Measurements show ~12 V present on Control Input Cable (+) 3 at its connected end, but only ~0.006 V at Control Switch 3 and Control Output Cable (+) 3. The continuity of Control Switch 3 is nominal (≈0.01 Ω), but Control Input Cable (+) 3 has its 'n' end floating and no longer connected to the switch, so the series path from the input to the switch and onward to the output is open at that disconnection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=165.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
